he ordinary, it offers a compelling portrait of the transformative powers embedded in day-to-day existence. From soccer fields to dinner tables, the everyday emerges as a moral laboratory for reshaping moral life. Cheryl Mattingly offers vivid and heart-wrenching stories to elaborate a first-person ethical framework, forcefully showing the limits of third-person renderings of morality.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAfrican American familieszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aChildren with disabilitiesxMedical carexMoral and ethical aspectszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aChronically ill childrenxMedical carexMoral and ethical aspectszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aMedical anthropologyzCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 0aMedical ethicszCaliforniazLos Angeles County. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aafrican american families.  aamerican dream.  aamerican studies.  aanthropology of morality.  aanthropology.  abreakdown.  achronic illness.  acultural studies.  aethical framework.  aethnographic research.  aeveryday occurances.  afamily.  afirst person perspective.  agenerational.  ahealth care.  ahealth.  ahuman condition.  alove.  amoral life.  amoral transformation.  amorality.  aparenthood.  apersonal experiences.  apolitics.  aradical change.  aserious chronic medical conditions.  astruggle for a good life.  atransformative power.  auncertainty.  aunited states of america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028119640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095953840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959538423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959538/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  Universi